{"id":"handbreadth","term":"Handbreadth","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A measure of four fingers, equal to about four inches (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 25:25\">Ex. 25:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 37:12\">37:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 39:5\">Ps. 39:5</a>, etc.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 25:25","Exodus 37:12","Psalms 39:5"]}